ly\nevolves as (1+z)^3, but the SFR-M* relation is independent of the environment\nsince z~2, as far as we rely on the H-alpha-based SFRs (with M*-dependent\nextinction correction). Even if we consider the possible environmental\nvariation in the dust attenuation, we conclude that the difference in the\nSFR-M* relation between cluster and field star-forming galaxies is always small\n(~<0.2dex level) at any time in the history of the Universe since z~2.\n[abridged]\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 21 Feb 2013 15:56:33 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Sat, 15 Jun 2013 15:26:34 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-15"}
